  "body": "\"Underflowed\" should be removed from the error message below. The correct term for integer arithmetic is \"overflow\" even if the number goes below 0. [Underflow](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arithmetic_underflow) refers to a floating point number becoming too small.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/dbf7c0b33001ebca01ac3737e8599ef251cf0de7/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/hardhat-network/stack-traces/panic-errors.ts#L16\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/dbf7c0b33001ebca01ac3737e8599ef251cf0de7/packages/hardhat-chai-matchers/src/internal/reverted/panic.ts#L23",
